#HELPS




0 PATRYN PATRYNS~
Patryn warriors do battle with and through their command of elemental
runes.  While once the runes a Patryn could draw on were as endless as
the concepts their minds could encompass, this is no longer the case.
However, runemagic of the present is still a potent force, which when
wielded with skill and cunning is a match for any form of magical or
spiritual attack.

 (*) Learn: learn how to use a given rune.
 (*) Tattoo: tattoo elemental runes onto the body.
 (*) Erase: a difficult to erase a rune from the body.
 (*) Runetrain: train in the use of primary runes.
 (*) Runestat: examine the runes on your body.
 (+) Runeweave: weave runes in the air to create magickal effects.
 (*) Circle: enhanced regen based on runetraining. 
 (*) Defenses: Raise or lower certain runic defenses.
 ( ) Inscribe: etch runes of power on weapons.
~

0 RUNETRAIN RUNETRAINING~
Syntax: runetrain <primary rune>
Example: runetrain earth

Runetraining is how patryns become adept in the use of the primary,
elemental runes.  These are Air, Earth, Fire, Water, Energy, and
Negative.  Runetraining is necessary to be able to runeweave
effectively, increases the power of tattoos,  and greatly enhances
a patryn's ability to close their circle.
~

0 DEFENSES~
Syntax: defenses <raise/lower>
Example: defenses lower
Example: defenses

The defenses command toggles whether a patryn's runic danger
sense is set off by attmpts to locate them.  Without an
argument, the command will report whether your defenses
are raised or lowered.
~

0 LEARN~
Syntax: learn <rune>
Example: learn destruction
Example: learn cost

Learning a rune is necessary for any use of a rune.  The cost of
learning a rune is in primal, and increases as you learn more
runes.  Typing 'learn cost' will display how much primal the next
rune will cost.  It is suggested that you learn the primary elements
first, as they are the most useful of the runes.
~

0 TATTOO TATTOING TATTOOING~
Syntax: tattoo <body part> <rune>
Example: tattoo rightleg water

By tattooing runes onto their bodies, Patryns enhance their combat
prowess.  Acceptable body parts are 'torso', 'leftarm', 'rightarm',
'leftleg' and 'rightleg'.  Only the primary runes of fire, air, earth
and water may be tattooed.  Here is an imcomplete list of the effects:

Torso:  Air   - Magickal Protection
        Earth - Toughness
        Fire  - Protection from Ki attacks
        Water - Enhanced regen
Arms:   Air   - Attacks
        Earth - Enhanced parry
        Fire  - Damage multiplier
Legs:   Earth - Anti parry/dodge
        Water - Enhanced dodge

Each rune costs primal, with costs increasing as the number of runes
per body part increase.
~

0 ERASE~
Syntax: erase <body part> <rune>
Example: erase leftarm air

Erasing magickal runes is a costly and time-consuming process,
requiring 25 primal and 1000 mana per erasure.  When a rune is
erased, the space on the body part becomes available again.
~

0 RUNESTATS~
Syntax: runetats

This provides a list of what runes are currently tattooed on your body.
It lists them by body part, and shows both used and available slots.
~

0 RUNEWEAVE RUNEWEAVING~
Syntax: runeweave <target> <primary rune> <secondary rune>
Example: runeweave fido fire death


~

0 LEGEND~
Legend is an abstract measurement of character 'presense', costing
both experience and status to train.  Legend ranks grant certain
minor abilities to all players, none of which are necessary to
be effective in pk, but which can be highly useful.

See LCOMMANDS for a list of said abilities.
~

0 LCOMMANDS~
Tricks of the trade which anybody can learn over time, only the more
experienced adventurer will learn abilities such as these.  Keep in
mind that they are merely useful abilities, not powerful combat
techniques.  Take them for what they are.

Legend  1:  Numeric damage           Legend  6:  Dare
Legend  2:  Gift                     Legend  7:  Reclaim
Legend  3:  Preserve                 Legend  8:  Humiliate
Legend  4:  Lenter & Lexit           Legend  9:  Soul Reaver 
Legend  5:                           Legend 10:  Challenge
~

0 GIFT~
When gift is implemented, it will allow you to transfer the ownership
of an item from yourself to another person.
~

0 LENTER LEXIT~
Syntax: lenter <phrase>
Syntax: lexit <phrase>

With these, you can modify the messages displayed upon your entering
and leaving chaosium.

Lenters and Lexits may not duplicate or emulate other system messages,
such as escape messages, or be intentionally deceptive.
~

0 RECLAIM~
This legend ability allows you to shift ownership of an item in your
possession from its previous owner to yourself.  This does, of course,
come at a cost.
~

0 HUMILIATE HUMILIATION~
Syntax: humilate <mortalled wounded schmuck>
Syntax: humiliation <amusing phrase>

Humiliate allows you to finish off players and display a finishing
message of your own creation.  The message is broadcast to the entire
mud in place of the normal finishing messages.  The humiliation command
is for setting this message.

Humiliations are broadcast to the mud, and as such are subject to certain
standards.  In practice, the only thing I don't want to see is messages
of a sexual nature.  Sex is one of the (very) few things here which is
consensual in nature.
~

0 SOULREAVER REAVER 'SOUL REAVER'~

When you finish off (not humiliate) an avatar, you drain their life
force and regain a percentage of your hit points.  How much depends
on how robust the victim was.
~

0 RULES COMMANDMENTS~
The Ten Commandments:
1) Kill and decapitate other immortals, or else:
2) Other immortals will kill and decapitate you.
3) Forgiveness may be devine, but vengeance is much more fun.
4) Don't whine or complain, or someone will kill you.
5) If someone whines or complains, you should kill them.
6) If someone doesn't whine or complain, kill them anyway.
7) Might makes right; a corpse will never betray you.
8) Friends are useful.  So is the exp you get for decapitating them.
9) Turn in bugs for rewards.  Abuse bugs and lose more than you gained.
10) Stop reading the stupid rules and let the slaughter commence!
~

0 POLICY POLICIES~
The purpose of all policies is to create an environment in which people
can compete, socialize, and generally have fun.  Punishments for infractions
are meant both as a deterrent, and as a guarantee that cheaters will not
prosper.  There are help files for each infraction listed below.  It is
strongly suggested that you read and obey them.

   MULTIPLAYING is banned, period.
   BOTTING is frowned upon and actionable.
   PUBLIC CHANNELS are for talking, not spamming.
   BUG ABUSE is highly illegal and will be punished severely.
   UNIQUES are not to be destroyed.
   CHAR SHARING is frowned upon.
   CHAR THEFT will result in the stolen char and the thief being banned.
   GIFT CAPPING is illegal.
   DUMBASS means do not be a dumbass.
   HARASSMENT this is a pk mud, it takes a LOT to be harassment.

   See the capitalized help files for more in depth explanations.

~


0 MULTIPLAYING~

Passing equipment or money between characters is just fine.  Anything
else, and I mean ANYTHING, is not fine.  This includes idling with more
than one character, grouping characters for exping or pkill, or ANYTHING
other than 30 seconds of swapping belongings.  I repeat, anything that
involves having two characters logged on at once, and not for a short
30 second equipment swap, is multiplaying.  Penalties will vary by
offense.
~

0 BOTTING~

This is defined as any actions which your character makes when the
player is not at the monitor.  There is really no need for botting,
as there are no spell levels or such to be botted up.  While botting
is not prohibited per se, 'bad things' may happen to botters, such as
my alerting the mud to what they're doing, dropping them in a no-exit
room, or in particularly irritating cases allowing players to get a
few caps on them.
~

0 PUBLIC 'PUBLIC CHANNELS'~

These exist so that people can socialize.  As such, people interfering
with their normal use (e.g. spamming) will lose their use.  Content
will for the most part be unpoliced; I am not easily offended.
~

0 BUGS ABUSE 'BUG ABUSE'~

If you find a a bug, or something you think is a bug, don't use it.
Don't "test" it, or play with it.. just report it on the bugs board.
If I deem you to have abused a bug, you will lose what you gained and
more.  Equipment related bugs (e.g. duping) will likely result in a
loss of equipment, character related bug abuse will likely result in
loss of character stats and abilities.  I will not hesitate to deny
and/or siteban repeat offenders; as somebody who has abused the hell
out of bugs on a number of muds, and seen how people pick up the habit
when the imms don't do shit, I know this to be absolutely necessary.
~

0 UNIQUES~

Destruction of a unique by any means (junking a container, saccing a
corpse, suiciding a char, etc etc) will result in the denial of all
a player's characters.  Uniques must be kept on the most played
character a player posesses, and if that character is not played and
pked with regularly the unique will be stripped.
~

0 CHARSHARING 'CHAR SHARING'~

Any sharing of characters or passwords is strongly discouraged.  If
you lose a character, you're shit out of luck.  Do yourself a favor;
always use different passwords on each character, and never use a
password here that you have used elsewhere.
~

0 CHARTHEFT 'CHAR THEFT'~

If I determine a character to be stolen, both the thief's characters
and the stolen character will be denied.  The reason for the latter
is simple: every instance of character theft costs me time to check
up on, and character theft is 99.99% of the time directly the result
of stupidity on the part of the former owner.  I am not a babysitter.
~

0 GIFTCAPPING 'GIFT CAPPING'~

This is defined as allowing other players to finish or humiliate your
character without fighting back.  Doing this once to settle a dispute
or matter of honor is not illegal; doing so multiple times, especially
to any and all takers, is.
~

0 DUMBASS COLUMBO PALON~

It shouldn't be necessary to spell this out, but don't be a fucking
dumbass.  Be a prick, a dick, a backstabber or whatever.. but don't
be a fucking dumbass.  I don't piss off easily.. if you manage to piss
me off, chances are it's because you were/are being a dumbass.
~

0 HARASSMENT~

This is a pk mud, with a pk atmosphere.  Somebody killing you a few
times, or keeping you morted for a few minutes, is not harassment.
I define harassment as a continual and systematic attempt to make
somebodys life miserable.  This isn't necessarily illegal except
in very extreme situations.  Use a little judgement.
~

0 GODWARS~
This is not a godwars mud per se; no actual godwars code from any release
has been used.  However, many of the concepts presented are borrowed from
the godwars system.  I'd like to thank KaVir for originally creating
godwars, and Coal and Puck for creating a truely good godwars mud.~

0 GWCOMMANDS~
There are a number of commands which are not indigenous to the Merc codebase
but are vital to playing on a godwars style mud.  Here are a few of them:

  FINISH, ESCAPE, SKILLS, LEVEL, BANDAGE
~

0 FINISH DECAPITATE~
Syntax: finish <mortally wounded avatar>
Example: finish sahra

When a player is mortally wounded, another avatar can finish them
off.  Known in the past as 'decpitation', finishing is possible with
any weapon, not just slashing and slicing.  If the victim is much
weaker, the finisher may become PARADOXED.~

0 ESCAPE~
Syntax: escape

When mortally wounded, an avatar can throw all pride to the wind and
attempt to escape.  They can't do this when tied up.  Escaping will
cause an avatar to lose whatever mana and stamina they had, and will
lag them for a short while.~

0 SKILLS~
Syntax: skills

This command gives you an analysis of your fighting skills in weapon
and stance.  If you are fighting somebody, it displays theirs as well.~

0 LEVEL LEVELS~
Syntax: level

This displays important information about your character's battle skills.
Stance and weaponskill ratings are shown, and for some classes additional
class specific information is displayed.
~

0 BANDAGE BANDAGES BANDAGING~
Syntax: bandage <target>
Example: bandage self

As not all classes have the mystick ability to heal, some form of first
aid was necessary to allow all classes to help their friends when wounded.
This is it.
~

0 STATS~
A characters statistics, or 'stats' as they are known, are measurements
of their strengths.  They range from 10 to 100, though not every class
can attain a rating of 100 in every stat.  See the help files on BODY,
MIND, SPIRIT, and WILLPOWER for more information.

Class        Body   Mind   Spirit   Willpower
Fist         90     75     100      80
Patryn       80     100    75       85
Saiyan       100    75     90       80
Sorcerer     75     90     80       100
Mazoku       95     95     95       95
~

0 BODY~
A characters body rating is a measurement of their overal physical
abilities, including strength, stamina, agility and general physical
wellbeing.  It affects damage done, damage recieved, how much one can
carry or wield, as well as how quickly your wounds heal.~

0 MIND~
Mind is an abstract measurement of a characters mental facility.  This
includes intelligence, cunning, and abstracts like problem solving
ability.  It affects resistance to mental attacks, how easy it is to
learn something, and especially ones abilities in rune magic.~

0 SPIRIT~
Spirit is an abstract measurement of, well, spirit.  How in touch with
themselves and the world around them, how wise they are, and well the
strength of their 'soul' or 'spirit', however you choose to call it.
Spirit is the driving force behind all Ki attacks and ki-based attacks,
and can help in resisting them.~

0 WILLPOWER~
Not so much a physical attribute, this is a measurement of a characters
strength of "will".  It can be described as drive, or as how much a
character can push themselves beyond their physical limits.  Magic, such
as it is, depends on a characters willpower.~

0 SAIYAN SAIYAJIN SAIYANS~
The Saiyan race is one much like the human race, save that they evolved
from monkeys as opposed to apes.  Though they are rumored to have once
had tails, this is no longer the case.  What sets the Saiyans, or
Saiya-jin as they are sometimes called, apart from other races is their
natural strength and propensity for battle.  They can charge and focus
their Ki more easily than any other race.

 (*) Technique: learn a saiyan battle technique.
 (*) Rage: Charge up power.
 (*) Focus: Spend power to enhance attributes.

 See HELP SAITECH for more information on Saiyan battle techniques.
 Also, see HELP STRENGTH, HELP SPEED, and HELP AEGIS.
~

0 RAGE~
Syntax: rage

Raging is the process by which Saiyans charge up their fighting power.
Rage costs movement points, and works based upon your body and spirit
ratings.  That is, the higher the body and spirit, the more power you
can charge up per rage.
~

0 TECHNIQUE~
Syntax: technique <argument>
Example: technique kamehameha
Example: technique cost
Example: technique learned

Technique is the command used to learn Saiyan battle techniques.  Most
of these are ways of inflicting damage with fighting power, while some
are useful noncombat abilities.  Typing 'technique' alone will list the
techniques, as well as two arguments, 'cost' and 'learned' which can be
entered to find out more information about techniques.

See 'help saitech' for a list of techniques and basic descriptions.
~

