0 FIST FISTS~
Fists are mystical warriors who shun the use of weapons.  While they can
wield them they will always be much more deadly using just their hands.
They have learned to focus their ki into amazing combinations, which have
the ability to lay waste to their opponents. Unfortunately a single
mistimed blow can cause these combinations to shatter, and many unexpected
results can occur.  When a true fist has learned to master every one of
their combinations, and practiced them to the point of perfection, there
is little that can stand in their way.

See Also:
Help basic, help combination, help fistki, help bodytrain, help discipline,
help newbiefist, help master
~

0 BASIC~ 
A fist must first learn to train in their basic moves by using the ‘master’
command.  There are low damage moves, but they are necessary in order to
execute the fist combinations.
~

0 MASTER~
Syntax: master <[move]/swap> [move1] [move2]
Example: master shinkick
Example: master ki
Example: master swap uppercut knee

Master is the command used by fists to learn master moves, increase
their max Ki, and swap the ki gain values of master moves. Learning a
master move costs 500,000 exp, as does training a point of Ki.

Swapping moves costs 150 primal.  To see what affect a swap will have,
look at 'master list' or master with no argument, to see your current
ki gain values for each move.  If shinkick is at 7, and jab is at 6, and
you master swap shinkick jab, shinkick will then have an average ki gain
of 6, and jab an average ki gain of 7.
~

0 COMBINATION COMBO~ 
Syntax: combo <phrase>
Example: combo
Example: combo dark

Combinations are the true power of fists.  They are executed by building up
the Fist’s ‘ki’ And then using the ‘Combo’ command.  Every ki from 10-30 has
a certain move attached to it.  Not all of them are beneficial so it is wise
to find a friend and spar them until you have tried out every combination.

Some combos, such as #29, have multiple moves associated with them.  They
can be accessed with an argument to the combo command.  For combo 29, the
acceptable arguments are 'dark' and 'holy'.
~

0 FISTKI~
A fist must activate their ki by using basic moves, but they must first train
there body to hold the power of that ki.  This is done by using the master
command.  Note:  The ki in prompt fist is NOT your max ki.  That is your active
ki, the one that is checked for combinations.
~

0 BODYTRAIN BODYTRAINING~
A Fist trains different parts of their body in order to become better fighters.
They can train their torso, their arms, their legs, and their hands. The command
to do this is ‘bodytrain.’  All bodyparts can be train up to 100.

Torso:  This affects toughness and regeneration
Arms:  This affects a fist’s blocking skill
Hands: This affects damage
Legs: This affects damage and dodge
~

0 DISCIPLINES~
Discipline is a rating of a Fist's.. well.. discipline.  You increase it by
typing 'discipline', and spending 500k per the level you wish to attain.
The ranks are:

1  eyesight     See in the dark, and see that which is unseen.
2  weaponskill  Unarmed skill can go up to 500. (auto)
3  stanceskill  Stances can go up to 300. (auto)
4  levitate     Levitate yourself.
5  roundhouse   A powerful attack that hits all enemies.
6  tackle       Prevent cowards from fleeing easily. (auto) 
7  innerfire    Attempt to burn away negative effects with Ki.
8  phoenixaura  Charge up spiritual energies to enhance combat abilities.
9  dim-mak      An attack which can poison the spirit of the victim.
~

0 NEWBIEFIST~ 
This is a small helpfile that should help a new fist get started.  There are
several things a new fist must do in order to be successful. 

1.  Prompt fist, this will put your ki in your prompt.  Without this
    combinations are nearly impossible.
2.  Each basic move has a set ki that will be added.  However to prevent the
    use of scripting and aliases this number will be modified by plus or minus
    one.  When trying to learn a move’s ki value, try it repeatedly until you
    see 3 different results.  The middle will be the true ki value.
    Example:  The true ki value of uppercut is two.  However there is a small
    chance of it being modified into either a one or three.
3.  Once you have learned the true ki values for all your basic moves, it is
    smart to alias them to the numbers on your keyboard.  This can make
    combinations much easier to perform.
4.  Every time you use the ‘combo’ command, your current ki is checked.  The
    combination assigned to that ki is performed.  It is wise to get a pen and
    pencil, and try every combination from ki 10 to ki 30.
5.  A Fist is one of the best tanks in the game.  Use this to your advantage.
6.  Max your unarmed and stance, this is the biggest factor in the damage you do.
~

