0 GWNEWBIE~ 
This is a help file for those of you who have never played godwars
before.  While this mud is not a Godwars code, it is modified to play
and act like it.  It is a heavy pk mud, and we do encourage you to rip
off as many heads as possible. The first major difference is there are
no levels here.  You gain strength by killing mobs for experience which
is then used to 'train' your statistics.  Experience is also used to buy
your class powers.  You can do this anywhere, you don't even have to be
near a guildmaster.  Also, we have edited  the Damroll and Hitroll formulas.
You are not penalized for having bad eq, instead it is an added bonus.
This means until you start to fight the HIGHEST mobs, and players, eq
isn't needed.  We feel this will help you get into the game faster, and
start having more fun. Overall this is a very fun code to play, and I hope
you enjoy it.

See also, Help: avatar, claim, train, level, practice, stance, status,
paradox, classes, godwars, gwcommands, legend
~

0 AVATAR~
An avatar is basically a pkiller.  You can become an avatar by training it.
This means mobs will no longer kill you, they will only send you to -10 hp.
If the mob is aggresive they will continue to do this until you use the
escape command.  Overall this mud should be newbie friendly, so there
shouldn't be anything stopping you from becoming an avatar.  The benefit of
having access to your class powers is huge, it will allowed you to gain
experience much faster.  Train avatar when you can, sure there may be an
asshole who kills you, but there are 5 other people willing to help you.
~

0 CLAIM~ 
When you claim ownership an item it costs 250 primal points.  What this
does is it makes you the owner of that item.  When you die the item will
travel with you, making it unlootable.  However if you drop the item or
lose it in some other way, it can be taken by anyone.  You will still be
the owner, but you will have to devise some plan to get it back into your
possession.  Ownership here is NOT like claim on other Godwars.  There is
no call command.  It is advised you claim ownership if only items you
wouldn't want to lose, and put the rest in a container you own.
~

0 TRAIN~
Training is how you increase your statistics.  You can train your
hp/mana/move here for experience.  The cost is equal to your current max
in that statistic.  If you have 5002 hp, it will cost 5002 experience for
that next point.  You can also train your body/mind/spirit/will power (see
help stat).  Primal is a way to channel your experience points, every point
has an increasing cost.  Primal is used to gain some classpowers.  Training
avatar will make you pkable, but it is also used to activate your class
powers.  That is basically all there is to training, and remember, train
anywhere, and everywhere!
~

0 LEVEL~
When you type level you will see three things: weapons, stances, and your
ratings in some class powers.  The weapons and stances can only be improved
by using them, and the classpowers are increased in various ways (depending
on your class).  The first section is the weapons.  It is advised you max
all weapons at 200.  Your chance to parry depends on your skill in your
opponents weapon.  If Bob is using claw, and I have 0 in it, I will not
parry many blows.  The same holds true for stances, you should max them all.
~

0 PRACTICE~
Practice will give you a short list of skills you can improve in.  This
costs experience.  The list of skills is short, because many of the other
things were useless, or we have added a different command to replace them.
Just practice everything to 100.
~

0 STANCE~
The first thing you should know about stances is the autostance command.
By typing 'autostance lion' you will automatically assume the lion stance
when combat begins (in most cases).  There are 2 rows of stances, the top
level being basic and the bottom being advanced.  Every advanced stance has
a prerequisite of 2 basic stances that must be master before it can be used.
The offensive stances are on the left and the defense are on the right.
You can also gain a small advatage in combat by outstancing your opponent.
In general a stance will beat the one one its left, for example eagle beats
hawk.  The one exception to this is hawk will defeat stork, making the circle
complete.  Everyone's stances are maxed at 200, the exception being the fist
class who gets them to 300.
~

0 AUTOSTANCE~
Syntax: autostance <some stance>

Autostance selects a stance which you will automatically assume when you
start fighting.  If you attack or whirlwind attack somebody, or they attack
you in these ways, your autostance will kick in.

For a list of stances, see level.
~


0 PARADOX~
2nd classes may safely finish 2nd classes.
1st classes may safely finish 1st classes.
Powerfuls my safely finish Powerfuls and above.

If a 1st class or higher finishes a character of a lower assessment, they
will be paradoxed for their cowardice: teleported to midgaard, mortally
wounded, and frozen for around thirdy seconds.

If a 2nd or 1st class kills above it's level, they will be deemed 'fair game',
and made cappable by anybody.  So.. don't escape cap far stronger players.
~

0 WHIRL~
Syntax: whirl

This skill allows you to execute a whirlwind attack, which hits everybody
in the room.  While not very accurate, it is a good way to get a fight going,
and as you spin around madly whacking everythign you may even hit things or
people you can't see.
~

0 SORCERER SORCERERS~
Sorcerers are human practitioners of the mystic arts.  They call on powerful
forces of good and evil, as well as natural spirits, to create supernatural
effects through force of will.  While often skilled with weapons by mortal
standards, they are spellcasters first and warriors second, and prefer to
attack with their magic.  While vulnerable in the physical sphere, they are
the most powerful in the mystic sphere since the corruption of Rune Magic.

 (*) Chant: Utter the words to activate a sorcerous spell.
 (*) Research: Learn more about a school of magic.
 (*) Specialize: Focus ones training on a particular branch of magic.
 (*) Concentrate: Toggle the conversion of mana to mystic energy.
 (*) Prepare: Select a school of magic to use for melee-round attacks.

See help files on: CHANT, RESEARCH, SPECIALIZE, MYSTIC, BLACKMAGIC,
WHITEMAGIC, WINDMAGIC, EARTHMAGIC, FIREMAGIC, WATERMAGIC, ASTRALMAGIC.

~

0 MYSTIC 'MYSTIC ENERGY'~
Mystic energy is the basis for sorcery, the raw power than is focused into
physical effects.  There is a finite limit on how much any human sorcerer
can hold at any time, however, and if they exhaust their store without
taking the time to replenish it, they will find it spread too thin in their
spells for them to have much effects.

A sorcerer's store of mystic energy restores itself slowly on it's own.
Sorcerers can increase the rate of restoration by concentrating their mana
into mystic energy.  See HELP CONCENTRATE.
~

0 CONCENTRATE~
Syntax: concentrate
Example: concentrate

The concentrate command toggles the conversion of mana into mystic energy.
When a sorcerer is concentrating, their mana will drop rapidly when it is
being used to refill their store of mystic energy.  With concentrate toggled
off, sorcerers can regenerate their mana.
~

0 CHANT~
Syntax: chant '<spell>' [target]
Example: chant 'balus rod' orc
Example: chant 'rubyeye blade'

Sorcerery is driven by words of power and invocations to dark, light, and
neutral spirits.  In come cases, only a couple words must be spoken, however
in the case of more powerful spells, several lines must be spoken.  The
spell need only be chanted once, and you will continue the chant until it
is complete or interrupted.
~

0 RESEARCH~
Syntax: research <school of magic>
Example: research black

Sorcerers learn more about the various schools of magic by researching them.
This costs primal, in increasing ammounts as the rank attained increases.
Sorcerers specialized in a given school can achieve a greater mastery of
that school than other sorcerers.  Specialists can achieve 50 ranks, while
the unspecialized can achieve 40.  Specialists also pay a slightly lower
cost for researching their chosen speciality.
~

0 SPECIALIZE~
Syntax: specialize <branch of magic>
Example: specialize white magic

Nearly all sorcerers focus their studies on one particular type of magic.
While this doesn't exclude them from learning other types, they become most
proficient in this one type.  The three branches of magic are Black magic,
White magic, and Shamanism.  It should be noted that while black and white
are schools of magic themselves, there are five schools of shamanistic magic.
Also, specializing for the first time is free, but a sorcerer wishing to
change specialty must overcome their past training, and pay a horrendous
cost for it.
~

0 CONCENTRATE~
Syntax: concentrate
Example: concentrate

Toggles whether a sorcerer concentrates their mana into mystical energy
quickly.  Without concentrating, no mana is spent, and mystical is regained
at approximately one point per second.  When concentrating, mana is spent
and mystical regained five times or more faster.
~

0 PREPARE~
Syntax: prepare <magic school/none>
Example: prepare astral

By preparing to use a school, sorcerers can substitute magical damage for
their melee round.  Only some spells are fast enough casting to be used
as such; the most powerful fast-casting spell you know in the chosen school
will be used.  Prepare none to switch back to normal melee.
~

