0 MULTIPLAYING MP~
One human player or equivalent non-human sentience may not control
more than one character at a time, period.

No two characters may be logged in from the same IP or computer.  Period.
I do not care in the least that your school network masks all computers
with the same IP, or that you're supposedly on a home network.

Being logged on at the password prompt, or the pause for the MOTD,
counts as being logged on.  Linkdead characters are also considered to
be logged on.  Hence, dropping link on one character and logging another
character on is multiplaying.

If you believe somebody is multiplaying, post a note to admin on the
personal board, with their names and the system time (displayed with the
time command).

`RMultiplaying will be punished by the denial of involved characters, and
additional punishment as seen fit by the admin.  This is considered one
of the most serious offenses.`n
~

