0 MAZOKU~
Indigenous to the astral plane, Mazoku are astral beings who
live off of the negative emotions of mortals.  Fear, anger, hatred,
despair.. all of these feed the Mazoku hunger.  Malicious and evil
in their own right, Mazoku revel in their feeding.  When they take
shape on the material plane, Mazoku may appear mortal, or monstrous,
depending on their purposes.  With a natural command of the astral
plane, Mazoku can easily effect what lesser beings would term "magic".

 (*) Morph: Change between the Mazoku's true, human, and battle forms.
 (*) Develop: The means by which Mazoku learn how to interact
              with the material plane.
 (*) Grow: Grow an additional limb or body part.
 (*) Form: Form arms into various weapons.
 (*) Charge: Charge up astral energies for attacks.
 (*) Release: Release astral attacks.
 (*) Reform: Spend essense to repair physical form.
 (*) Astrike: Deadly attack from the astral plane.
 (*) Lash, Rake, Gouge: innate abilities of weapon forms.
 (*) Instantiate: Mold essense into a physical item.
 (*) Imbue: Spend essense to increase the strength of an astral item.

See helps for EGO, NIHILISM, ESSENSE, MATTER, and ASTRAL.
~

0 LASH RAKE GOUGE~
Syntax: lash
Syntax: rake
Syntax: gouge

With claws formed, a mazoku can rake their claws across an enemy
for quick and easy damage.

With tentacles formed, a mazoku can attempt to trip up an enemy
with lash, knocking them out of stance.

With spikes formed, a mazoku can jab their spikes into an enemy's
eyes, attempting to blind them.
~

0 MORPH~
Syntax: morph <form>
Example: morph battle

Mazoku are astral beings, and can exist in several forms on the
material plane.  Battle forms are hideous but effective in combat,
human form is useful for disguise, and in true form a Mazoku naturally
regenerates any damage taken.
~

0 DEVELOP~
Syntax: develop <ability>
Example: develop astrike

Develop is the means by which Mazoku acquire new abilities or
increase their skills in handling material and astral energies.
~

0 GROW~
Syntax: grow <body part>
Example: grow fourth

Mazoku can grow extra body parts for additional attacks, flight,
and enhanced material vision.
~

0 FORM~
Syntax: form <weapon>
Example: form blades

Mazoku can form their arms into weapons, each of which has
advantages and disadvantages.
~

0 CHARGE~
Syntax: charge <color of energy>
Example: charge obsidian

By charging up astral energies, Mazoku can prepare powerful
attacks with properties which vary by color.
~

0 RELEASE~
Syntax: release <attack type> <target>
Example: release bolt clout

When Mazoku have astral energies charged up, they can release
the energies as an attack in the form of blasts, bolts, or
bomb-like explosions all around them.
~

0 ASTRIKE~
Syntax: astrike

While in true form, mazoku can strike from the astral plane,
often appering right behind their target when they re-enter
the material plane.
~

0 REFORM~
Syntax: reform

Mazoku may repair any physical manifestation they inhabit with
their own essense.
~

0 INSTANTIATE~
Syntax: instantiate <equipment>
Example: instantiate cloak

By molding their essense into physical objects, Mazoku can create
items which are essentially part of them.  This is important, as
Mazoku disdain the use of almost all material items as unnecessary.

Astral items are linked to the Mazoku who created them; if such an
item becomes seperated from the Mazoku, it will fade from existance.
~

0 IMBUE~
Syntax: imbue <astral item>
Example: imbue ring

Imbuing is a means by which Mazoku may increase the strengt and
power of their astral equipment by pouring their own essense into it.
~

0 EGO~

Mazoku exist primarily through their own will to live, hence their
Ego is of utmost importance.  The more sure of onesself a Mazoku
is, the more powerful they are.  Killing things of at least moderate
challenge is fulfilling, while using powerful attacks against lesser
beings is a sign of weakness.
~

0 NIHILISM~

Within every Mazoku is a deep-seated need to destroy all of existance,
including itself.  As a Mazoku's need to destroy increases, it can
dominate their thoughts and actions.  Nihilisic Mazoku will likely
strike with greater abandon and do little to defend themselves.
~

0 ESSENSE~

Mazoku are beings of the astral plane, composed of astral energy.
Essense is another name for this energy, which Mazoku harvest
from mortals by causing them pain and death.
~

0 MATTER~

Matter is a measure of how competent a Mazoku is in handling
their material form, and actions on the material plane.
~

0 ASTRAL~

Astral is a measure of how competent a Mazoku is in handling
their astral form, as well as astral energies and attacks.
~

